     5→//! JJK chalk command - empty commits marking steeplechase events
     6→//!
     7→//! The chalk command creates empty commits with special formatting for tracking
     8→//! steeplechase events like approach, wrap, fly, or heat-level discussions.
     9→
    10→use std::io::{self, BufRead};
    11→
    12→use crate::jjrf_favor::{jjrf_Coronet as Coronet, jjrf_Firemark as Firemark};
    13→use crate::jjrn_notch::{jjrn_ChalkMarker as ChalkMarker, jjrn_format_session_message, jjrn_format_chalk_message, jjrn_format_heat_discussion};
